==Classical Nahuatl==
===Other spellings===
*[[ypalhnemoani]]
===Etymology===
''[[ipal]]'' "through him/her/it/them" + ''[[nemohuani]]'' "people in general habitually live", from ''[[nemohua]]'' "people in general live", from ''[[nemi]]'' "he/she/it/they live"
===Noun===
'''īpalnemohuani'''

# One through which people live.
===Usage note===
Used to describe various gods, including [[Titlacahuan-Tezcatlipoca]], [[Quetzalcoatl]], and the Christian [[God]].
